title: N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 20 §§ 1-1.12 - Tangible personal property
content:
N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 20 §§ 1-1.12 - Tangible personal property

State Regulations

Tax Law, section 208(11)

The term "tangible personal property" means corporeal
personal property such as machinery, tools, implements, goods, wares and
merchandise. It includes audio works, audiovisual works, literary works, visual
works, graphic works or games, delivered via a physical medium that are not
subject to the rules for digital products under section 210-A(4). It does not
mean money, deposits in banks, shares of stock, bonds, notes, credits or
evidences of an interest in property, or evidences of debt. Notes
